## Risk Assessment

### Technical Risks

| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|--------|-----------|
| Database schema changes | High | Validate schema.sql matches expectations; document assumptions |
| Connection pool tuning for CLI | Medium | Research short-lived connection patterns; implement sensible defaults |
| FULLTEXT search performance | Medium | Test with realistic data volumes; add indexes if needed |
| Cross-platform compatibility | Low | Use stdlib and well-maintained libraries; test on multiple OS |
| Tag deduplication logic | Medium | Handle case-sensitivity and whitespace consistently |

### Execution Risks

| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |
|------|--------|-----------|
| Scope creep (web UI, etc.) | Medium | Strictly follow spec; defer out-of-scope items |
| Over-engineering database layer | Medium | Start simple (direct SQL); refactor only if needed |
| Incomplete error handling | High | Systematic error handling review; test error paths |
| Poor UX (confusing commands) | Medium | Follow Unix conventions; user testing with quickstart guide |

## Dependencies

### External Dependencies
- MySQL/MariaDB 10.11+ (user-provided)
- Go 1.21+ toolchain
- Standard Unix tools (make, git)

### Internal Dependencies
- Phase 1 must complete before Phase 2 starts
- Repository layer must be tested before command implementation
- Configuration loading must work before commands can function

### Dependency Management
- Use Go modules (go.mod/go.sum)
- Pin dependency versions
- Minimal dependency philosophy (only essential libraries)
- Prefer stdlib over third-party when reasonable

